The ‘Menaechmei’ belonged to the first comedies imi- tated in modern literature. The earliest regular comedy of modern times was founded on the Menaechmei. This is the Carandra of Bibbiena (afterwards a cardinal); it was represented at Venice in 1508, though not published , till 15241. It would seem that the ‘Oalandra’ was also
